{%- comment -%}
  educator-product
  ----------------
  Single source of truth for "is this an educator-only product?".

  An educator product is one served by the educator product template
  (template_suffix 'educator') OR carrying any educator-* merchandising
  tag (educator-only, educator-sensory-play, educator-nature-play,
  educator-creative-arts, educator-dramatic-play, educator-steam, etc.).

  These products are published to the Online Store so signed-in educators
  can open their PDPs, but they must NOT surface to retail shoppers (e.g.
  in search / predictive search). Retail and educator share one storefront
  gated by the customer tag, so the separation has to happen at render time.

  Usage (outputs the string 'yes' for an educator product, otherwise nothing):
    {%- capture is_edu -%}{%- render 'educator-product', product: item -%}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- if is_edu contains 'yes' -%} ... {%- endif -%}
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign is_edu = false
  if product.template_suffix contains 'educator'
    assign is_edu = true
  endif
  unless is_edu
    for t in product.tags
      if t contains 'educator-'
        assign is_edu = true
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endunless
  if is_edu
    echo 'yes'
  endif
-%}
